Package: kinship
Version: 1.1.4
Date: 2026-06-25
Title: Mixed-Effects Cox Models, Sparse Matrices, and Modeling Data from Large Pedigrees
Authors@R: c(person("Beth", "Atkinson", email="atkinson@mayo.edu", role="aut", comment="Pedigree functions"), person("Terry", "Therneau", email="therneau@mayo.edu", role="aut", comment="All other functions"), person("Jing Hua", "Zhao", email="jinghuazhao@hotmail.com", role="cre"))
Maintainer: Jing Hua Zhao <jinghuazhao@hotmail.com>
Depends: R (>= 2.8.0), methods, survival, nlme, lattice
Description: It consists of three major parts: 'coxme' for
    mixed-effects Cox models; 'kinship' for routines to create and
    manipulate n by n matrices describing the genetic relationships
    among individuals; and 'pedigree' for creating and plotting
    pedigrees. The 'bdsmatrix' class provides sparse block-diagonal
    matrices used to store kinship matrices, together with 'gchol' for
    generalized Cholesky decompositions.
